text.__SUMMARY__: Conus aito, common name Paladin cone snail, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.This snail is predatory and venomous and is capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail occurs off French Polynesia.
text.References: Rabiller M. & Richard G. (2014). Conus (Gastropoda, Conidae) from offshore French Polynesia: Description of dredging from TARASOC expedition, with new records and new species. Xenophora Taxonomy. 5: 25-49. page(s): 37, pl. 5, figs 1-4, 7-12
